<div class="body-title">
  Is it Safe?
</div>
<div class="body">
  Xanthan gum is a food additive that is generally considered safe. <br>
  It’s a common gluten-free substitute for baking or cooking. <br>
  Thickeners that contain xanthan gum, like Simply Thick, are not recommended
  for infants due to increased risk of infection and death. <br>
  The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) considers xanthan gum to be Generally Recognized as Safe (GRAS).
</div>
